@NODE DEST "Introduction"
@PREV INFO
@NEXT REQU

  EjectCD is designed for opening and closing CD tray.
  EjectCD works with Archos Overdrive/Zappo CD drive (probably also with
  other drives controlled by cd.device).
@ENDNODE

@NODE REQU "Requirements"
@PREV DEST
@NEXT INST

  EjectCD needs any Amiga with KS v37 or higher.
@ENDNODE

@NODE INST "Installation"
@PREV REQU
@NEXT PARMS

  Copy program with icon to desired place on disk.
@ENDNODE

@NODE PARMS "Arguments"
@PREV INST
@NEXT ATTN

  For CLI/Shell:

  X : horizontal window position.
  Y : vertical window position.
  PUBSCREEN or PS : public screen name where EjectCD opens window.

  For Workbench:

  X,Y,PUBSCREEN - same as for CLI/Shell. Write it in "Tool Types" window
                  of icon.

  Example usage:
  EjectCD X 500 Y 200 PS DOPUS.1
@ENDNODE

@NODE ATTN "Important"
@PREV PARMS
@NEXT AUTH

  When program can't open cd.device, then "flashes" display.
  In some situations (e.g. when you mount drive but drive is empty),
  EjectCD can't open tray (drive signalizes opened tray).
@ENDNODE

